answers.answer: I'm going to see if somebody from MedHelp can help you with your Sugar Sense app question.C~

Hi there -You already have done this. :)If you go to your home page, you can see the info you have entered has synced to our site -http://www.medhelp.org/personal_pages/show/4910659?personal_page_id=4910659It's in your health feed.If you'd like to see it in a tracker, you can add the Diabetes Tracker here -http://www.medhelp.org/health_tools/#/trackersYou can then set it up, and see your data in a chart form.Please feel free to let me know if you have any questions, or send us an email by tapping on App Support in the side menu in the app.Emily
